# Go Style And Testing

Go style and testing.

- Idiomatic Go. Wrap errors with fmt.Errorf and %w. Pass ctx context.Context first on I/O methods. Use defer for cleanup.
- Write the test before or with the code. Use table-driven tests.
- For every ASN.1 structure: a round-trip test, and a known-answer test wherever the spec or SGP.33-1 gives example bytes.
- Validation and verification code must fail closed; write the negative tests first.
- Unit tests run against the in-memory Store with no database. Integration tests use real Postgres in Docker.
